<br>
I also am order neutral.  As order neutral I percieve myself as seeking balance in all things and this balance is much easier achieved through an adherence to order.  Both good and evil have their place in the world, but both strive to form the world into a place of extremes, I consider a haughty High elf follower of Tunare(OG), and a Haughty Dark elf follower of Innoruk (OE) in the same light, both believe in order, but neither follows a path that can succeed in bringing order to the world.  These followers of good or evil necessarily sow discord in their interactions with the world through their efforts to enforce one particular form of order, and are in truth doing more service to discord.  For your particular case (is ON even an option for a high elf?) you could roleplay a dissafected priest.  Perhaps the infighting and politics of your clerical order have tainted the cause of good in your eyes, you have traveled some, and in these travels you have seen that there is a lack of balance in the world.  Good acts can result in evil outcomes, evil acts can result in good. Things, people, are not 2 dimensional, a Shadowknight is capable of  good, a Palladin can do evil, though of course they lack the impartiality to see their actions in this way.....  Only the measured response of an impartial judge can truly determine the best course of action.  After all, as a follower of good, you cannot possibly provide medical services for an ogre Shadowknight of Cazic thule, such as my friend Ichi, and as misguided as he is, he provides balance for the equally misguided Erudite Palladins of the world, and may in fact provide  a net balance of order (or even goodness) to the world as a result of his career,  if he spends time battling Innoruk in the Plane of Hate, and the dragons and other races of the world that seek to bring disorder and chaos to Norrath.<br>
<br>
No, Marrik, you are right to seek the middle path, pass not judgement on those who follow order, as good and evil are two sides of the same coin.  Rather in your travels seek not to succor those who promote discord, no matter how noble or evil are their intentions in doing so. <p>Lorec <br>
Wandering Judge of the Tribunal <br>

Lousy Tailor <br>
Better Brewer <br>
